The paper presents a novel 3D deep convolutional neural network (CNN)-based method for MR image contrast classification. The focus is on image processing techniques, such as tissue segmentation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method uses deep learning techniques, which is a popular area of research in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses neural networks for classification, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
